Positive Test Cases
Test Case 1: Successful Email Composition
Preconditions: The user is logged in to their Gmail account.
Steps:
Click on the "Compose" button.
Enter the subject as "Incubyte".
Enter the body as "QA test for Incubyte".
Click on the "Send" button.
Expected Result: The email is sent successfully with the correct subject and body.

Test Case 2: Email Composition with Attachment
Preconditions: The user is logged in to their Gmail account.
Steps:
Click on the "Compose" button.
Enter the subject as "Incubyte".
Enter the body as "QA test for Incubyte".
Attach a file to the email.
Click on the "Send" button.
Expected Result: The email is sent successfully with the correct subject, body and attachment.

Test Case 3: Email Composition with CC and BCC
Preconditions: The user is logged in to their Gmail account.
Steps:
Click on the "Compose" button.
Enter the subject as "Incubyte".
Enter the body as "QA test for Incubyte".
Enter a CC recipient email address.
Enter a BCC recipient email address.
Click on the "Send" button.
Expected Result: The email is sent successfully with the correct subject, body, CC and BCC recipients.

Negative Test Cases
Test Case 1: Empty Subject
Preconditions: The user is logged in to their Gmail account.
Steps:
Click on the "Compose" button.
Leave the subject field empty.
Enter the body as "QA test for Incubyte".
Click on the "Send" button.
Expected Result: An error message is displayed and the email is not sent.

Test Case 2: Empty Body
Preconditions: The user is logged in to their Gmail account.
Steps:
Click on the "Compose" button.
Enter the subject as "Incubyte".
Leave the body field empty.
Click on the "Send" button.
Expected Result: The email is sent successfully with an empty body.

Test Case 3: Invalid Recipient Email Address
Preconditions: The user is logged in to their Gmail account.
Steps:
Click on the "Compose" button.
Enter the subject as "Incubyte".
Enter the body as "QA test for Incubyte".
Enter an invalid recipient email address.
Click on the "Send" button.
Expected Result: An error message is displayed and the email is not sent.

Test Case 4: Cancel Email Composition
Preconditions: The user is logged in to their Gmail account.
Steps:
Click on the "Compose" button.
Enter the subject as "Incubyte".
Enter the body as "QA test for Incubyte".
Click on the "Cancel" button.
Expected Result: The email composition is cancelled and the email is not sent.

Test Case 5: Email Composition with Invalid Attachment
Preconditions: The user is logged in to their Gmail account.
Steps:
Click on the "Compose" button.
Enter the subject as "Incubyte".
Enter the body as "QA test for Incubyte".
Attempt to attach an invalid file type to the email.
Click on the "Send" button.
Expected Result: An error message is displayed and the email is not sent.

BDD-Style Test Cases

Positive Scenarios
